content.description: Start with a left hand on the horn and a right hand on the good undercling. Work your way up the arete and transition to the steep face for the top out at the apex of the boulder.
content.location: Left arete of the Jaws boulder.

content.description: The Sit Start to Jaws.  Start on lower right side of the boulder with your right hand on a sidepull and left hand on a crappy sloper.  Move up with bad feet to Jaws start and finish as Jaws.
content.protection: Two to three pads and a spotter.  The landing can be bad with poor pad placement.
content.location:
Same boulder as

Jaws

.  Go up above

World's Best

and through the Corridor.

content.description: Long, tall, lip traverse (moving right to left) up the north side of the boulder. Problem starts on excellent holds along the lip and moves up across edges, crimps and pinches. Very sequence dependent. Gain the apex and make a scary mantle up over the lip on good holds. Fantastic Problem.
content.protection: At least 3 crash pads but the more the better.
content.location: Off to the right side of the zeke's wall climbers trail, about 20 meters north of "Worlds Best" on the obvious overhanging fin.
